album.title: Texas Flood
album.artist: Stevie Ray Vaughan and Double Trouble

track.name: Rude Mood

artist.name: Stevie Ray Vaughan and Double Trouble

comments: If you can't play the blues... you might as well hang it up.
Don't waste your time away thinkin' 'bout yesterday's blues.
I think Stevie started doing something like this as the song before their break.  I remember hearing it at Threadgill's in Austin and thinking it was good enough for an album.  Be dang- it was!
I could live without SRV; not into guitar slingers especially. But I enjoy a good, straight-ahead up tempo piece that isn't overwhelmed with the "look-at-me" guitar.
live fast,die young,and leave a good corpse was a motto for many, back then!!!
Good people die too early. www.jackybullfrog.com
Just to even play 3 strings like Stevie!
and that's how it's done in Texas!
NO one does it better than SRV!!!!!!!
